<table width="100%" style="margin-top:10px">
<tr>
	<td>
		<h2>SPOJ Problem Set (classical)</h2>
				<h1>7859. Upper Right King (Hard)</h1>
		<h2>Problem code: ADV04B1</h2>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>

<p align="justify">
<p>There is a king in the lower left corner of the n × n checkmate board. The king can move one step right, one step up or one step up-right. How many ways are there for him to reach the upper right corner of the board?

<h3>Input</h3>
<p>The first line of input contains number T - the amount of test cases. Next T lines consist of single integer n - the size of the board.

<h3>Constraints</h3>
<p>1 <= T <= 10000<br />
1 <= n <= 1000000

<h3>Output</h3>
<p>For each test case output the munber of ways to reach upper right corner of n × n board modulo 1000003.

<h3>Example</h3>

<pre>
<b>Input:</b>
2
2
3

<b>Output:</b>
3
13

</pre>


